cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper proposes a novel method for learning how algorithms perform through genetic evolution. The paper focuses on a case study in clustering, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the creation of populations of datasets, which falls under the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents an open source implementation, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
